1119
01:55:57,460 --> 01:55:59,060
I can't feel my legs.

1120
01:56:10,420 --> 01:56:13,890
In this week of Thanksgiving,
there is much for which we can be grateful

1121
01:56:14,090 --> 01:56:17,260
as you look back to where we stood,
only four weeks ago.

1122
01:56:17,540 --> 01:56:20,530
The unity of this hemisphere,
the support of our allies

1123
01:56:20,690 --> 01:56:23,110
and the calm determination of the American people.

1124
01:56:23,580 --> 01:56:26,160
These qualities may be tested many more times

1125
01:56:26,380 --> 01:56:27,580
in this decade.

1126
01:56:30,640 --> 01:56:34,870
So how many students do you think you'll have here?
Once you get the academy up and running.

1127
01:56:35,350 --> 01:56:39,060
As many as I can manage. Possibly more.

1128
01:56:41,960 --> 01:56:46,360
You know, one day the government is going
to realize how lucky they were,

1129
01:56:46,550 --> 01:56:48,180
..to have Professor X on their side.

1130
01:56:49,740 --> 01:56:52,000
I suppose I am a real professor, aren't I.

1131
01:56:52,000 --> 01:56:53,580
Next thing I'll be going bald.

1132
01:56:55,320 --> 01:56:57,430
We're still on the governmentâ€™s side, Moira.

1133
01:56:57,980 --> 01:57:00,540
Still G-men, just without the G.

1134
01:57:00,910 --> 01:57:03,640
No, you're your own team now.

1135
01:57:04,420 --> 01:57:05,500
It's better.

1136
01:57:06,530 --> 01:57:09,160
You're "X-Men".

1137
01:57:11,310 --> 01:57:12,730
Yes, I like the sound of that.

1138
01:57:13,240 --> 01:57:18,960
Moira, for us anonymity will be the first line of defense.

1139
01:57:18,960 --> 01:57:20,230
I know.

1140
01:57:21,810 --> 01:57:25,380
They can threaten me all they want, Charles.

1141
01:57:26,190 --> 01:57:28,360
I'll never tell them where you are.

1142
01:57:28,940 --> 01:57:29,940
Ever.

1143
01:57:30,830 --> 01:57:32,430
I know you won't.

1144
01:57:34,250 --> 01:57:35,260
My love.

1145
01:57:42,580 --> 01:57:44,790
I remember the attack on HQ.

1146
01:57:45,350 --> 01:57:47,030
Leaving to go somewhere else.

1147
01:57:47,660 --> 01:57:50,710
And then this morning, I woke up at home.

1148
01:57:51,520 --> 01:57:52,520
That's it.

1149
01:57:53,690 --> 01:57:55,800
All that time wiped clean from your mind.

1150
01:57:56,150 --> 01:57:57,240
Just gone.

1151
01:57:57,600 --> 01:57:59,550
He can do that.
You don't remember anything?

1152
01:58:00,100 --> 01:58:07,550
Sometimes I get fragments.
Like trees, sunlight.

1153
01:58:09,620 --> 01:58:12,350
- A kiss.
- Aw, Jesus.

1154
01:58:12,870 --> 01:58:16,220
Gentlemen, this is why the CIA
is no place for a woman.

1155
01:58:21,040 --> 01:58:22,120
What the hell was that?

1156
01:58:38,160 --> 01:58:40,300
I know we've had our differences.

1157
01:58:42,830 --> 01:58:46,580
- Where's your telepath friend?
- Gone.

1158
01:58:47,580 --> 01:58:50,590
Left a bit of a gap in my life.
If I'm to be honest.

1159
01:58:50,590 --> 01:58:52,460
